  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 9</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 10</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 23 | <b>Successes:</b> 3</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 11 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 24</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> Mob</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You plant your elbow into the target, delivering a powerful blow. The attack cannot target held objects, but ignores any hardness of 8 or lower when striking other objects. Make an unarmed attack that deals 4d6 bonus damage, plus 1d6 per 4 levels (up to 9d6 total bonus damage). If you use the Power Attack feat, you gain a +2 damage bonus per point of attack penalty taken instead of the normal bonuses from that feat. This attack can be made as part of a charge.<br><br>If hit, the target is knocked back a number of feet equal to the damage done (rounded down to the nearest 5 ft increment) (Fortitude negates). If the target hits a solid object of its size or larger, it suffers 2d6 fall damage, as though it had fallen 20 ft. You suffer a -4 penalty to Learn checks when learning this technique if you do not have the Gouken feat.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
